    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Made of ivory or metal, sometimes embellished with incised decorations of animals such as bears or seagulls. Made by Yup'ik families for their female children. Using the knife to draw in various surfaces, Yup'ik girls retell important histories, share personal experiences, or sing songs. </Note_Text>
